<li id="cite_note-110"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-110">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGoodmanGalatiotoThorpeNamdeo2016" class="citation journal cs1 cs1-prop-long-vol">Goodman, Paul S.; Galatioto, Fabio; Thorpe, Neil; Namdeo, Anil K.; Davies, Richard J.; Bird, Roger N. (1 April 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.envint.2016.02.002">"Investigating the traffic-related environmental impacts of hydraulic-fracturing (fracking) operations"</a>. <i>Environment International</i>. 8990: 248260. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.envint.2016.02.002">10.1016/j.envint.2016.02.002</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26922565">26922565</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Environment+International&amp;rft.atitle=Investigating+the+traffic-related+environmental+impacts+of+hydraulic-fracturing+%28fracking%29+operations&amp;rft.volume=89-90&amp;rft.pages=248-260&amp;rft.date=2016-04-01&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.envint.2016.02.002&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F26922565&amp;rft.aulast=Goodman&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+S.&amp;rft.au=Galatioto%2C+Fabio&amp;rft.au=Thorpe%2C+Neil&amp;rft.au=Namdeo%2C+Anil+K.&amp;rft.au=Davies%2C+Richard+J.&amp;rft.au=Bird%2C+Roger+N.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%252Fj.envint.2016.02.002&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-111"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-111">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFVaughan2016" class="citation news cs1">Vaughan, Adam (24 February 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2016/feb/24/fracking-traffic-would-increase-local-air-pollution-study-tankers-water-nitrogen-oxide-emissions">"UK fracking traffic would increase local air pollution, finds study"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">9 April</span> 2017</span>. <q>Additionally the report's conclusions fail to take into account, that in the UK, water is more often available through pipelines, so there is no need to transport it across the country by truck.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=UK+fracking+traffic+would+increase+local+air+pollution%2C+finds+study&amp;rft.date=2016-02-24&amp;rft.aulast=Vaughan&amp;rft.aufirst=Adam&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2016%2Ffeb%2F24%2Ffracking-traffic-would-increase-local-air-pollution-study-tankers-water-nitrogen-oxide-emissions&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-112"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-112">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protect-groundwater-and-prevent-groundwater-pollution/protect-groundwater-and-prevent-groundwater-pollution">"Chapter 2"</a>. <i>Protect groundwater and prevent groundwater pollution</i>. Environment Agency<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 March</span> 2017</span>. <q>Water stored below the ground in rocks or other geological strata is called groundwater. The geological strata that hold water are called aquifers. Groundwater may rise to the surface through naturally occurring springs, or be abstracted using boreholes and wells. Groundwater may also naturally flow into rivers (called base flow) and support wetlands, forming part of local ecosystems.The legal definition of groundwater is: 'All water which is below the surface of the ground in the saturation zone and in direct contact with the ground or subsoil.'Aquifers are: 'A subsurface layer or layers of rock or other geological strata of sufficient porosity and permeability to allow either a significant flow of groundwater or the abstraction of significant quantities of groundwater.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Chapter+2&amp;rft.btitle=Protect+groundwater+and+prevent+groundwater+pollution&amp;rft.pub=Environment+Agency&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fpublications%2Fprotect-groundwater-and-prevent-groundwater-pollution%2Fprotect-groundwater-and-prevent-groundwater-pollution&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-113"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-113">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.bgs.ac.uk/research/groundwater/shaleGas/methaneBaseline/results.html">"Results summary - National methane baseline survey of UK groundwaters - British Geological Survey (BGS)"</a>. <i>Bgs.ac.uk</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">6 March</span> 2019</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Bgs.ac.uk&amp;rft.atitle=Results+summary+-+National+methane+baseline+survey+of+UK+groundwaters+-+British+Geological+Survey+%28BGS%29&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bgs.ac.uk%2Fresearch%2Fgroundwater%2FshaleGas%2FmethaneBaseline%2Fresults.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-114"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-114">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.raeng.org.uk/publications/reports/shale-gas-extraction-in-the-uk">"Shale gas extraction in the UK: a review of hydraulic fracturing &#124; Summary Recommendation 1"</a>. Royal Academy of engineering<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">5 March</span> 2017</span>. <q>To detect groundwater contamination, the UK's environmental regulators should work with the British Geological Survey (BGS) to carry out comprehensive national baseline surveys of methane and other contaminants in groundwater. Operators should carry out site-specific monitoring of methane and other contaminants in groundwater before, during and after shale gas operations</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Shale+gas+extraction+in+the+UK%3A+a+review+of+hydraulic+fracturing+%26%23124%3B+Summary+Recommendation+1&amp;rft.pub=Royal+Academy+of+engineering&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.raeng.org.uk%2Fpublications%2Freports%2Fshale-gas-extraction-in-the-uk&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-115"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-115">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2015/7/section/50">"2015 Infrastructure Act"</a>. UK Legislation<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">13 September</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=2015+Infrastructure+Act&amp;rft.pub=UK+Legislation&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.uk%2Fukpga%2F2015%2F7%2Fsection%2F50&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-116"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-116">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20160911223407/http://www.ciwem.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Shale-Gas-and-Water-2016.pdf">"Shale Gas and Water 2016 An independent review of shale gas extraction in the UK and the implications for the water environment"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i>Ciwem.org</i>. CIWEM. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ciwem.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Shale-Gas-and-Water-2016.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on 11 September 2016<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">31 August</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Ciwem.org&amp;rft.atitle=Shale+Gas+and+Water+2016+An+independent+review+of+shale+gas+extraction+in+the+UK+and+the+implications+for+the+water+environment&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ciwem.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F02%2FShale-Gas-and-Water-2016.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-117"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-117">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAmec_Foster_Wheeler_Environment_&amp;_Infrastructure_UK_Ltd2016" class="citation web cs1">Amec Foster Wheeler Environment &amp; Infrastructure UK Ltd (October 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://ec.europa.eu/environment/integration/energy/pdf/Study_on_the_management_of_environmental_impacts_and_risks_of_conventional_oil_and_gas%20.pdf">"Study on the assessment and management of environmental impacts and risks resulting from the exploration and production of hydrocarbons"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. European Commission. p.&#160;277<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">1 April</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Study+on+the+assessment+and+management+of+environmental+impacts+and+risks+resulting+from+the+exploration+and+production+of+hydrocarbons&amp;rft.pages=277&amp;rft.pub=European+Commission&amp;rft.date=2016-10&amp;rft.au=Amec+Foster+Wheeler+Environment+%26+Infrastructure+UK+Ltd&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fenvironment%2Fintegration%2Fenergy%2Fpdf%2FStudy_on_the_management_of_environmental_impacts_and_risks_of_conventional_oil_and_gas%2520.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-118"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-118">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.raeng.org.uk/publications/reports/shale-gas-extraction-in-the-uk">"Shale gas extraction in the UK A review of hydraulic fracturing, chapter 4.3.3"</a>. <i>RAENG</i>. Royal Academy of Engineering. p.&#160;37<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">22 February</span> 2017</span>. <q>The very unlikely event of fractures propagating all the way to overlying aquifers would provide a possible route for fracture fluids to flow. However, suitable pressure and permeability conditions would also be necessary for fluids to flow. Sufficiently high upward pressures would be required during the fracturing process and then sustained afterwards over the long term once the fracturing process had ceased. It is very difficult to conceive of how this might occur given the UK's shale gas hydrogeological environments. Upward flow of fluids from the zone of shale gas extraction to overlying aquifers via fractures in the intervening strata is highly unlikely</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=RAENG&amp;rft.atitle=Shale+gas+extraction+in+the+UK+A+review+of+hydraulic+fracturing%2C+chapter+4.3.3&amp;rft.pages=37&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.raeng.org.uk%2Fpublications%2Freports%2Fshale-gas-extraction-in-the-uk&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-119"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-119">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBoothroydAlmondQassimWorrall2016" class="citation journal cs1">Boothroyd, I.M.; Almond, S.; Qassim, S.M.; Worrall, F.; Davies, R.J. (2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.scitotenv.2015.12.096">"Fugitive emissions of methane from abandoned, decommissioned oil and gas wells"</a>. <i>Science of the Total Environment</i>. <b>547</b>: 4619. <a href="/wiki/Bibcode_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Bibcode (identifier)">Bibcode</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2016ScTEn.547..461B">2016ScTEn.547..461B</a>. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.scitotenv.2015.12.096">10.1016/j.scitotenv.2015.12.096</a></span>. <a href="/wiki/PMID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="PMID (identifier)">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26822472">26822472</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Science+of+the+Total+Environment&amp;rft.atitle=Fugitive+emissions+of+methane+from+abandoned%2C+decommissioned+oil+and+gas+wells&amp;rft.volume=547&amp;rft.pages=461-9&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F26822472&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.scitotenv.2015.12.096&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F2016ScTEn.547..461B&amp;rft.aulast=Boothroyd&amp;rft.aufirst=I.M.&amp;rft.au=Almond%2C+S.&amp;rft.au=Qassim%2C+S.M.&amp;rft.au=Worrall%2C+F.&amp;rft.au=Davies%2C+R.J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%252Fj.scitotenv.2015.12.096&amp;rfr_id=info%