<li id="cite_note-192"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-192">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMasoncorrespondent2014" class="citation web cs1">Mason, Rowena; correspondent, political (10 August 2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2014/aug/10/fracking-censored-house-price-report">"Fracking campaigners criticise 'censored' report on house prices"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">6 March</span> 2019</span> &#8211; via www.theguardian.com.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Fracking+campaigners+criticise+%27censored%27+report+on+house+prices&amp;rft.date=2014-08-10&amp;rft.aulast=Mason&amp;rft.aufirst=Rowena&amp;rft.au=correspondent%2C+political&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2014%2Faug%2F10%2Ffracking-censored-house-price-report&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-193"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-193">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://d3n8a8pro7vhmx.cloudfront.net/nwenergy/pages/102/attachments/original/1429019521/JLL_report_-_NWETF_house_prices_(2).pdf?1429019521">"Residential research report: The Impact of On-Shore Gas Exploration Activities on Local House Prices"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. JLL/NorthWest Energy Task Force<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">14 March</span> 2017</span>. <q>From 1995 to 2014, Preese Hall has seen a higher trajectory of house price growth when compared with Lancashire and the North West. Although Preese Hall saw a larger decline in house prices between the application being submitted and implementation than Lancashire and the North West, the area has seen a price growth of 7.5% between onshore gas operations commencing in 2011 and 2014. This compares with the North West seeing a prices increase by 0.2% whereas Lancashire saw a price decline of 4.2%. Taken together, there is no clear evidence based on this data to suggest that onshore gas operations have had a material impact on local house prices. 34% of households within three miles [5&#160;km] of the subject site fall into the category of Affluent Achievers. A further indication of the prosperity in the area is that 71% of households are owner/occupied</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Residential+research+report%3A+The+Impact+of+On-Shore+Gas+Exploration+Activities+on+Local+House+Prices&amp;rft.pub=JLL%2FNorthWest+Energy+Task+Force&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fd3n8a8pro7vhmx.cloudfront.net%2Fnwenergy%2Fpages%2F102%2Fattachments%2Foriginal%2F1429019521%2FJLL_report_-_NWETF_house_prices_%282%29.pdf%3F1429019521&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-194"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-194">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation news cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2017/jan/04/friends-of-earth-ticked-off-claims-anti-fracking-leaflet">"Friends of the Earth ticked off over claims in anti-fracking leaflet"</a>. 4 January 2017<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">14 March</span> 2017</span>. <q>Other claims made in the ad, entitled "Pat saved her home from fracking. You can save yours too", included that there would be "plummeting house prices"<span class="cs1-kern-right"></span></q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Friends+of+the+Earth+ticked+off+over+claims+in+anti-fracking+leaflet&amp;rft.date=2017-01-04&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2017%2Fjan%2F04%2Ffriends-of-earth-ticked-off-claims-anti-fracking-leaflet&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AFracking+in+the+United+Kingdom" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
</ol></div>
